<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="navbar">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="logo">CMS</div>
            <ul class="nav-links">
                <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a></li>
                <li><a href="/about" class="active">About</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="container">
        <h1><%= title %></h1>

        <section class="about-content">
            <h2>About This Application</h2>
            <p>
                This is a sample CMS (Content Management System) web application built with Node.js and Express,
                deployed on Azure Container Apps using Terraform Infrastructure as Code.
            </p>

            <h3>Technology Stack</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> Node.js 18 (Alpine)</li>
                <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Express.js</li>
                <li><strong>Template Engine:</strong> EJS</li>
                <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> Azure Container Apps</li>
                <li><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Terraform</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Architecture</h3>
            <p>
                This application runs on Azure Container Apps, which provides a serverless container platform
                with auto-scaling capabilities (1-3 replicas). All traffic is routed through:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Azure Front Door (Global CDN)</li>
                <li>Azure DNS (Domain routing)</li>
                <li>Application Gateway (WAF + SSL)</li>
                <li>Container App (This application)</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>üìù Article management and viewing</li>
                <li>üìä Dashboard with statistics</li>
                <li>üîå RESTful API endpoints</li>
                <li>‚ù§Ô∏è Health check endpoint</li>
                <li>üìà Performance monitoring</li>
                <li>üîí Enterprise-grade security</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>API Endpoints</h3>
            <div class="api-endpoints">
                <div class="endpoint">
                    <code>GET /health</code>
                    <p>Health check endpoint for Container Apps</p>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint">
                    <code>GET /api/articles</code>
                    <p>Retrieve all articles</p>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint">
                    <code>GET /api/articles/:id</code>
                    <p>Retrieve a specific article</p>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint">
                    <code>POST /api/articles</code>
                    <p>Create a new article</p>
                </div>
                <div class="endpoint">
                    <code>GET /status</code>
                    <p>Application status and metrics</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Deployment Information</h3>
            <p>
                This application is containerized and deployed using Azure Container Apps.
                It automatically scales between 1-3 replicas based on CPU and memory usage.
            </p>

            <h3>Support</h3>
            <p>
                For issues or questions about this CMS application, please refer to the GitHub repository
                at <code>asdad-emizzy/Azure-Terraform-Templates</code>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2025 Azure CMS. Built with Terraform and Container Apps.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
